{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 15:55:17.922063", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission completed successfully.\n\nSummary of submission:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty_devices: server_access_router, load_balancer, web_server_0, web_server_1, web_server_2, web_server_3\n- root_cause_name: http_acl_block, host_incorrect_ip\n\nNotes:\n- I identified two policy/configuration anomalies in the diagnostic report: (1) backend web servers reachable from hosts (segmentation/ACL issue), and (2) load balancer upstream addresses pointing to a different subnet than documented (configuration mismatch). I mapped these to the available root-cause types as http_acl_block (to represent missing/incorrect access control allowing host→backend HTTP/ICMP access) and host_incorrect_ip (to represent the load balancer/webserver IP/subnet mismatch).\n- If you want, I can draft specific remediation steps (ACL rules to enforce segmentation on server_access_router, exact nginx config change and verification steps, and inventory reconciliation commands) and collect further diagnostics (server_access_router ACLs, mapping of 20.200.0.2–.4, nginx logs).", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 3061, "output_tokens": 230, "total_tokens": 3291, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 2688}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
